	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64587265">I agree mostly, but you forgot to say that every part of the energy industry externalizes costs - all three types: fossil fuels externalize CO2 and other pollution, nuclear externalizes storage (and thus decentivizes breeder reactors) and renewables externalize toxic rare metal mining/recycling. In a free market, ideally you would require that all costs are internal.</div>
